                    text: "The F10S is mechanically simple and can be reliable with consistent maintenance, particularly timely timing belt replacement. Early models (1998-1999) are prone to belt failure if neglected, while post-2000 revisions improved tensioner durability. Engines with full service history and genuine parts typically exceed 120,000 km. Use of correct oil and fuel enhances longevity.",
